Text: Now then, another long day ahead of us!
When are we going home, Gamma?

Going home?! We can't leave now! We've just uncovered
a new business opportunity!

I'm here today to try out different menu items based
on yesterday's tuna sandwich.

Eta may think it's fine to laze around all day, but
I've got a job to do!

*sigh* Alright, well, good luck. I'll be over here
taking it easy.

Come on, Zeta. The least you could do is help a
little...

Pretty sure I'll end up helping more than a little. I
mean, Gamma, you can hardly clean a fish let alone
cook it.
Um, well...yeah...but...
...I'm good at frying potatoes!

Your enthusiasm is palpable, I'll give you that...
Oh well.

Alrighty, let's fish, fish, fish, and pump out lots
and lots of products!

Damn it, why do monsters keep showing up and getting
in our way? Zeta!
Quit ignoring me and help me take them out!

What did you expect, to just sit there in quiet
contemplation making french fries? The smell
of food cooking might attract monsters.
But...they didn't turn up yesterday!
Yesterday, we had a land breeze.

Today the wind's blowing from the sea, so of course
monsters around here are gonna come sniffing.
Well, anyway, good luck.
"Good luck"? Seriously?
Oh, come on!
Huff...huff... L-Looks like that's all of them...

...Sear the tuna fillet and thinly spread the tartar
sauce on the baguette.

Could be worth trying to mix in some fish sauce.
Although the spices may be a little overpoweringâ€”

Look at you, leisurely making sandwiches while I'm
fending off monsters!
Here, have a taste.
Huh? Oh, thanks, Zeta. Don't mind if I do.
...It's good...but the aroma is quite intense.

Really? That's kind of what I like about it. Think
it'll also go well with chicken, carrots, and onions.

Still, it's more of an acquired taste. Not something
that'll appeal to a larger customer base.

I'm just asking about the taste, not talking
business.
But of course, I'm gonna talk business.
Not me. I'll take some of the fries.
Oh wait, I still haven't salted them.

Didn't you wash them in seawater before deep-frying
them? That salt should be plenty.

Right, didn't think of that... What's in the bottle,
Zeta?
Malt vinegar. It's vinegar made from barley.
Vinegarâ€”w-wait, noooo! You put on way too much!

You're supposed to pour vinegar all over the fries
until they're drenched. I saw construction workers
doing it in the capital.
...Yeah, not bad. Give it a try, Gamma.

You sure? I'm pretty picky with how I like my
potatoes!
...Whoa! They're delicious!

A sweet, tangy vinegar intertwined with savory friesâ€”
It's as if the amber waves of a fall harvest are crashing
against cliffs of crumbling, golden potatoes!
Again with the weird analogies...

Tuna sandwiches, fries with malt vinegar...I'm
starting to see the recipe for success!

Next, let's try dousing the tuna sandwiches in
vinegar as well.

Huh! That's taking it too far! It's already got
tartar sauce inâ€”
*splash*
Whaaat?!

Ohh, look what you've done! Half the bread is
soaked! It's hardly the same dish now...
*munch*

Whoa...this is also pretty good! Come on, Gamma, give
it a try.

Uck... Zeta, there's something seriously wrong with
your taste budsâ€”
It's actually reeeally goood!
Talk about a 180...

It's certainly a bold move, but the fried tuna and
malt vinegar go beautifully together!

They draw out the acidity of the tartar sauce while
still leaving a mellow taste in your mouth.

If this hasn't already caught on in the capital, it's
a huge business opportunity waiting to happen!
...And she's back to talking business.

Maybe we should try it with some of the other fish
as well...
